  "informal_statement": "For every pair of integers a, b: gcd(a, b) is expressible as an integer linear combination of a and b -- there exist integers u, v with gcd(a,b) = a*u + b*v.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Cited directly via Mathlib's Int.gcdA/Int.gcdB (the extended-Euclidean-algorithm Bezout coefficients) and Int.gcd_eq_gcd_ab (the identity relating them to gcd).",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem bezout (a b : ℤ) : ∃ u v : ℤ, (Int.gcd a b : ℤ) = a * u + b * v",
